# Walkthrough — Aurelia Guard Backend Integration

## What Was Built

A complete **FastAPI backend** (`backend/`) and full **frontend wiring** to replace all mock data with real persistence and real face detection/recognition.

---

## Backend (`backend/`)

### Structure
```
backend/
├── main.py                          # FastAPI app, CORS, lifespan (camera startup)
├── database.py                      # SQLAlchemy + SQLite (PostgreSQL-ready)
├── requirements.txt                 # Python dependencies
├── .env / .env.example              # Environment variables
├── README.md                        # Setup & run instructions
├── models/
│   ├── staff.py                     # Staff table (with face_embedding BLOB)
│   ├── log.py                       # LogEntry table
│   ├── settings.py                  # Settings (single JSON row)
│   └── recipient.py                 # AlertRecipient table
├── schemas/
│   ├── staff.py                     # camelCase Pydantic schemas
│   ├── log.py
│   ├── settings.py                  # Nested hours/rules/channels + DEFAULT_SETTINGS
│   ├── recipient.py
│   └── box.py                       # Detection box schema (WebSocket payload)
├── routers/
│   ├── staff.py                     # CRUD + multipart photo upload + embedding
│   ├── settings.py                  # GET/PUT with auto-seed defaults
│   ├── logs.py                      # Filtered listing
│   ├── alerts.py                    # Recipients CRUD + test alert dispatch
│   ├── dashboard.py                 # KPI summary + 7-day detections chart
│   └── stream.py                    # MJPEG boundary stream
├── services/
│   ├── face_recognition_service.py  # dlib/face_recognition + Haar cascade fallback
│   ├── rule_engine.py               # Store hours, maintenance, cooldown, alert logic
│   └── alert_dispatcher.py          # WhatsApp (Twilio), siren (winsound), door lock (stub)
├── cv/
│   └── camera.py                    # Background thread: capture → detect → rule engine → alert
├── ws/
│   └── handler.py                   # WS /ws/detections — pushes Box[] at ~300ms
└── storage/
    ├── photos/                      # Uploaded staff face photos
    └── snapshots/                   # Alert capture images
```

### Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| **camelCase JSON aliases** | Pydantic `alias_generator=to_camel` so the wire format matches TypeScript types — zero frontend type changes |
| **Settings as single JSON row** | Avoids complex relational mapping for nested hours/rules/channels; Pydantic is the source of truth |
| **face_recognition fallback** | If dlib can't be installed (common on Windows), falls back to OpenCV Haar cascade — server still starts |
| **Independent alert channels** | WhatsApp, siren, and door lock dispatch independently; one failure doesn't block the others |
| **Midnight-crossing maintenance** | `is_maintenance_active()` correctly handles windows like 22:00→05:00 |
| **Alert on ANY face during closed hours** | Per the original spec — not just unknowns |

